            </div><!--  
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <note>Translated by Mehari Worku with Wendy Laura Belcher, edited by Wendy Laura Belcher, Jeremy Brown, Mehari Worku & Dawit Muluneh  <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML6598">EMML (HMML) 6598, f. 178r, in 2023.</note>
             <ab>A miracle [performed] by Our Holy Lady Mary, the Twofold Virgin, the Mother of Divinity, may her prayer and blessings be with us forever and ever, amen.
Listen to what Our Lady did for her servant, the one named Gabra Maryam. She brought him a golden throne, on which shone twelve lights and twelve stars, and it was round like a bowl.
She also showed him a luminous city, one that exists in the mind of the Trinity, and which no one has ever seen before.
Gabra Maryam asked Our Lady Mary, “Who will enter this city? Who will sit on this throne?”
She said, [thereby ensuring it would be his future,] “You will be their chief!” After saying this, she blessed him and ascended to heaven.
May her prayer and blessings be with her servant forever and ever, amen.</ab>
